http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/TN-lorry-driver-killed/article14005098.ece

A truck driver was killed on the spot, and five other passengers on board an APSRTC bus were injured when the two vehicles collided head-on in Gandhi Nagar locality on the outskirts of Palamaner town, 40 km from here, on Sunday morning.According to police, the bus belonging to Alipiri Depot in Tirupati was on returning from Bengaluru and the empty truck which was on its way towards Kolar collided. The deceased truck driver has been identified as Selvam (27), a native of Dindigal in Tamil Nadu, and his body has been shifted to area hospital for autopsy. The injured in the bus were rushed to a government hospital nearby. A case has been registered.